focus_stack uses a mixed-license layout.

1. Original project-authored code

These paths are licensed under GPL-3.0-only in this repository:

- `src/**/*.zig`
- `scripts/*.sh`
- `build.zig`
- `flake.nix`
- `flake.lock`
- `README.md`
- `docs/**`
- `tests/**`
- `vendor/smooth-numbers/**`

The full GPL-3.0-only text is in `COPYING`.

This bucket is the main project-authored implementation and support code. It is
kept separate from the reference/oracle and optional upstream-reference
buckets below so that any future additional license grant for the original
implementation can be made explicitly and narrowly.

2. Reference / oracle tooling

These files are developer tooling used to compare behavior against upstream
implementations and are intentionally kept out of the "original
project-authored" bucket above:

- `tools/enfuse_pyramid_oracle.cpp`
- `tools/vigra_oracle.cpp`
- `tools/hugin_config.h`

These files are licensed under GPL-3.0-only as separate reference/oracle
tooling. See `tools/README.md`.

3. Optional fetched third-party and upstream reference material

When fetched locally with `scripts/fetch_upstream_refs.sh`, these paths retain
their own upstream licenses, notices, and provenance:

- `upstream/**`

See `THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md` and the license files inside those fetched trees.

4. Notes on scope

- A future permissive or dual-license grant for the original project-authored
  implementation would not automatically apply to `tools/**` or to any fetched
  `upstream/**` material unless stated explicitly.
- `vendor/smooth-numbers/**` is treated as project-authored code in this
  repository and included in the GPL-3.0-only bucket above. If that submodule is
  distributed independently, it should carry an explicit license notice in its
  own repository as well.
